{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, Z is also downward directed.",
    "So Z is a filter.",
    "Moreover, if ⊥ ∈ Z, then ⊥ = ∅ ∈ F, in which case F would not be a proper filter in (A g) b.",
    "Thus, Z is a proper filter in A.",
    "Finally, by our definitions,P g (Z) = { x | Z ∈ x} = { x | x ∈ Z} = F.For part 2, the left-to-right direction follows from part 1."
  ]
}